  "shortBio": "Hollowshades of Void Hollow, titled “Umbralpath Companion,” are independent void-touched Riftlings—shape-fluid and hard to pin. In the wild they stay independent, shape-fluid and hard to pin, and attentive to micro-changes in mist and echo-dust. Favorites include Voidcap. In Void Hollow, they favor Voidcap and teach quieter routes to those who listen.",
  "standardBio": "Hollowshade, titled among keepers as “Rifthush Scout,” carries careful distance in every movement. Native to Void Hollow, the species slips through mist and echo-dust, leaving traces that other Riftlings can follow like soft maps. Wild groups form loose bonds rather than rigid packs; a independent individual may become the emotional center of a small hearthline. They eat Voidcap eagerly and dislike food that smells of neglect or spoilage. Ancient keepers carved Hollowshade silhouettes into travel stones, believing the species guided the lost. Modern hatcheries record them as reliable companions; their practical problem-solving intelligence makes training feel like conversation. Their signature ability, Rift Slip, reflects a life shaped by Void Hollow more than by arena ambition. Their quiet is mistaken for emptiness. In truth they are listening harder than louder species. Young Hollowshades practice Rift Slip as play long before they understand battle. Adults teach by demonstration: where to rest, what to avoid, how to share warmth or shade.",
  "fullLore": "Hollowshades first condensed from residual hollowsilence along the living edges of Void Hollow after early Rift fractures cooled into weather. Their eggs appear where mist and echo-dust gathers into stillness—never in the loudest danger, always in the pocket of calm beside it. Early surveyors mistook them for ambient phenomena until a Hollowshade returned a dropped lantern, carefully, as if returning a promise.\n\nIn ancient eras, regional peoples treated Hollowshades as omen-bearers rather than pets. Carvings show them walking ahead of caravans, pausing at unstable ground, and curling around children during ashfall or fog. The species was never “tamed” in the old sense; it chose. That choice culture survives in modern Riftkeeper etiquette: you do not yank a Hollowshade into a bond. You invite, wait, and keep the invitation honest.\n\nModern history is quieter and more practical. Hatcheries map Hollowshade care cycles with the same seriousness given to rare lines, because common does not mean shallow. Void Hollow still holds wild populations that trade soft greetings with passerby pets. After major Rift events, Hollowshades often appear first at recovery centers—not as heroes, but as inventory clerks of comfort, counting who is cold, hungry, or afraid.\n\nNatural behavior is independent at the core and adaptable at the edges. They are shape-fluid and hard to pin, companion-sized, easy to cradle, and communicate through body posture and scent marks. Socially, they prefer small trusted circles; strangers are assessed by scent, posture, and whether a keeper’s voice stays kind under stress. Intelligence presents as practical problem-solving intelligence. They sleep in shallow scrapes and prefer weather that matches their affinity’s comfort band.\n\nEcologically, Hollowshades act as seed dispersers of calm within Void Hollow. Allies often include Riftslug and Mistwraith; rivalries with Lanternjay and Cindercub are usually about nesting space or shiny refuse, not blood feuds. Predators are rare—most threats come from collapsing terrain and careless machines rather than jaws.\n\nCulture around them is affectionate and slightly superstitious. Travelers once claimed that following a wild Hollowshade through Void Hollow would lead them past a Rift storm unharmed. Collectors prize unusual cosmetics, yet marketplace notes remind buyers that verified care history matters more than glitter. The common misunderstanding remains: Their quiet is mistaken for emptiness. In truth they are listening harder than louder species. The hidden truth keepers debate in soft rooms is simpler and stranger: When deeply bonded, a Hollowshade shares short dream-images of places it has never physically visited.\n\nFrom egg to evolved form, their life story stays continuous. Eggs look like glazed stones veined with void light. Hatchlings are clumsy with sincerity; adults become specialists of place; evolved stages sharpen instinct without erasing childhood habits. Battle tendencies favor swift harassment, and evolution philosophy insists transformation should answer lived experience—not fashion.\n\nFor Riftkeepers, a Hollowshade is a living chapter of Void Hollow. Feed it Voidcap, respect its independent tempo, and it will teach you the region’s quieter grammar: which winds lie, which stones remember, which silences are safe. Personal quests often begin with a shell symbol, a remembered scent, or a dream of a door that only opens when the bond is honest. That is the Hollowshade bargain—not destiny sold at rarity price, but a life that continues because you showed up.",
